    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112Sa/90</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3114. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1737. Embassy’s 2865, October 16, 8 p.m., your 1683. Plan suggested does not
                    meet with the approval of the Department. We <pb facs="0179" n="1013"
                        xml:id="pg_1013"/> are now in consultation with Department with view to
                    preparing a revised plan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
